244/**
245 * Writes the SDVOB or SDVOC with the given value, but always writes both
246 * SDVOB and SDVOC to work around apparent hardware issues (according to
247 * comments in the BIOS).
248 */
249static void intel_sdvo_write_sdvox(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo, u32 val)
250{
251 struct drm_device *dev = intel_sdvo->base.base.dev;
252 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
253 u32 bval = val, cval = val;
254 int i;
255
256 if (intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg == PCH_SDVOB) {
257 I915_WRITE(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg, val);
258 POSTING_READ(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg);
259 /*
260 * HW workaround, need to write this twice for issue
261 * that may result in first write getting masked.
262 */
263 if (HAS_PCH_IBX(dev)) {
264 I915_WRITE(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg, val);
265 POSTING_READ(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg);
266 }
267 return;
268 }
269
270 if (intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg == GEN3_SDVOB)
271 cval = I915_READ(GEN3_SDVOC);
272 else
273 bval = I915_READ(GEN3_SDVOB);
274
275 /*
276 * Write the registers twice for luck. Sometimes,
277 * writing them only once doesn't appear to 'stick'.
278 * The BIOS does this too. Yay, magic
279 */
280 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
281 {
282 I915_WRITE(GEN3_SDVOB, bval);
283 POSTING_READ(GEN3_SDVOB);
284 I915_WRITE(GEN3_SDVOC, cval);
285 POSTING_READ(GEN3_SDVOC);
286 }
287}

289static bool intel_sdvo_read_byte(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo, u8 addr, u8 *ch)
290{
291 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
292 {
293 .addr = intel_sdvo->slave_addr,
294 .flags = 0,
295 .len = 1,
296 .buf = &addr,
297 },
298 {
299 .addr = intel_sdvo->slave_addr,
300 .flags = I2C_M_RD,
301 .len = 1,
302 .buf = ch,
303 }
304 };
305 int ret;
306
307 if ((ret = i2c_transfer(intel_sdvo->i2c, msgs, 2)) == 2)
308 return true;
309
310 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("i2c transfer returned %d\n", ret);
311 return false;
312}

435static void intel_sdvo_debug_write(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo, u8 cmd,
436 const void *args, int args_len)
437{
438 int i, pos = 0;
439#define BUF_LEN 256
440 char buffer[BUF_LEN];
441
442#define BUF_PRINT(args...) \
443 pos += snprintf(buffer + pos, max_t(int, BUF_LEN - pos, 0), args)
444
445
446 for (i = 0; i < args_len; i++) {
447 BUF_PRINT("%02X ", ((const u8 *)args)[i]);
448 }
449 for (; i < 8; i++) {
450 BUF_PRINT(" ");
451 }
452 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(sdvo_cmd_names); i++) {
453 if (cmd == sdvo_cmd_names[i].cmd) {
454 BUF_PRINT("(%s)", sdvo_cmd_names[i].name);
455 break;
456 }
457 }
458 if (i == ARRAY_SIZE(sdvo_cmd_names)) {
459 BUF_PRINT("(%02X)", cmd);
460 }
461 BUG_ON(pos >= BUF_LEN - 1);
462#undef BUF_PRINT
463#undef BUF_LEN
464
465 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%s: W: %02X %s\n", SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo), cmd, buffer);
466}

478static bool intel_sdvo_write_cmd(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo, u8 cmd,
479 const void *args, int args_len)
480{
481 u8 *buf, status;
482 struct i2c_msg *msgs;
483 int i, ret = true;
484
485 /* Would be simpler to allocate both in one go ? */
486 buf = kzalloc(args_len * 2 + 2, GFP_KERNEL);
487 if (!buf)
488 return false;
489
490 msgs = kcalloc(args_len + 3, sizeof(*msgs), GFP_KERNEL);
491 if (!msgs) {
492 kfree(buf);
493 return false;
494 }
495
496 intel_sdvo_debug_write(intel_sdvo, cmd, args, args_len);
497
498 for (i = 0; i < args_len; i++) {
499 msgs[i].addr = intel_sdvo->slave_addr;
500 msgs[i].flags = 0;
501 msgs[i].len = 2;
502 msgs[i].buf = buf + 2 *i;
503 buf[2*i + 0] = SDVO_I2C_ARG_0 - i;
504 buf[2*i + 1] = ((const u8*)args)[i];
505 }
506 msgs[i].addr = intel_sdvo->slave_addr;
507 msgs[i].flags = 0;
508 msgs[i].len = 2;
509 msgs[i].buf = buf + 2*i;
510 buf[2*i + 0] = SDVO_I2C_OPCODE;
511 buf[2*i + 1] = cmd;
512
513 /* the following two are to read the response */
514 status = SDVO_I2C_CMD_STATUS;
515 msgs[i+1].addr = intel_sdvo->slave_addr;
516 msgs[i+1].flags = 0;
517 msgs[i+1].len = 1;
518 msgs[i+1].buf = &status;
519
520 msgs[i+2].addr = intel_sdvo->slave_addr;
521 msgs[i+2].flags = I2C_M_RD;
522 msgs[i+2].len = 1;
523 msgs[i+2].buf = &status;
524
525 ret = i2c_transfer(intel_sdvo->i2c, msgs, i+3);
526 if (ret < 0) {
527 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("I2c transfer returned %d\n", ret);
528 ret = false;
529 goto out;
530 }
531 if (ret != i+3) {
532 /* failure in I2C transfer */
533 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("I2c transfer returned %d/%d\n", ret, i+3);
534 ret = false;
535 }
536
537out:
538 kfree(msgs);
539 kfree(buf);
540 return ret;
541}

543static bool intel_sdvo_read_response(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo,
544 void *response, int response_len)
545{
546 u8 retry = 15; /* 5 quick checks, followed by 10 long checks */
547 u8 status;
548 int i, pos = 0;
549#define BUF_LEN 256
550 char buffer[BUF_LEN];
551
552
553 /*
554 * The documentation states that all commands will be
555 * processed within 15Âµs, and that we need only poll
556 * the status byte a maximum of 3 times in order for the
557 * command to be complete.
558 *
559 * Check 5 times in case the hardware failed to read the docs.
560 *
561 * Also beware that the first response by many devices is to
562 * reply PENDING and stall for time. TVs are notorious for
563 * requiring longer than specified to complete their replies.
564 * Originally (in the DDX long ago), the delay was only ever 15ms
565 * with an additional delay of 30ms applied for TVs added later after
566 * many experiments. To accommodate both sets of delays, we do a
567 * sequence of slow checks if the device is falling behind and fails
568 * to reply within 5*15Âµs.
569 */
570 if (!intel_sdvo_read_byte(intel_sdvo,
571 SDVO_I2C_CMD_STATUS,
572 &status))
573 goto log_fail;
574
575 while ((status == SDVO_CMD_STATUS_PENDING ||
576 status == SDVO_CMD_STATUS_TARGET_NOT_SPECIFIED) && --retry) {
577 if (retry < 10)
578 msleep(15);
579 else
580 udelay(15);
581
582 if (!intel_sdvo_read_byte(intel_sdvo,
583 SDVO_I2C_CMD_STATUS,
584 &status))
585 goto log_fail;
586 }
587
588#define BUF_PRINT(args...) \
589 pos += snprintf(buffer + pos, max_t(int, BUF_LEN - pos, 0), args)
590
591 if (status <= SDVO_CMD_STATUS_SCALING_NOT_SUPP)
592 BUF_PRINT("(%s)", cmd_status_names[status]);
593 else
594 BUF_PRINT("(??? %d)", status);
595
596 if (status != SDVO_CMD_STATUS_SUCCESS)
597 goto log_fail;
598
599 /* Read the command response */
600 for (i = 0; i < response_len; i++) {
601 if (!intel_sdvo_read_byte(intel_sdvo,
602 SDVO_I2C_RETURN_0 + i,
603 &((u8 *)response)[i]))
604 goto log_fail;
605 BUF_PRINT(" %02X", ((u8 *)response)[i]);
606 }
607 BUG_ON(pos >= BUF_LEN - 1);
608#undef BUF_PRINT
609#undef BUF_LEN
610
611 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%s: R: %s\n", SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo), buffer);
612 return true;
613
614log_fail:
615 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%s: R: ... failed\n", SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo));
616 return false;
617}

829static void intel_sdvo_get_dtd_from_mode(struct intel_sdvo_dtd *dtd,
830 const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
831{
832 uint16_t width, height;
833 uint16_t h_blank_len, h_sync_len, v_blank_len, v_sync_len;
834 uint16_t h_sync_offset, v_sync_offset;
835 int mode_clock;
836
837 memset(dtd, 0, sizeof(*dtd));
838
839 width = mode->hdisplay;
840 height = mode->vdisplay;
841
842 /* do some mode translations */
843 h_blank_len = mode->htotal - mode->hdisplay;
844 h_sync_len = mode->hsync_end - mode->hsync_start;
845
846 v_blank_len = mode->vtotal - mode->vdisplay;
847 v_sync_len = mode->vsync_end - mode->vsync_start;
848
849 h_sync_offset = mode->hsync_start - mode->hdisplay;
850 v_sync_offset = mode->vsync_start - mode->vdisplay;
851
852 mode_clock = mode->clock;
853 mode_clock /= 10;
854 dtd->part1.clock = mode_clock;
855
856 dtd->part1.h_active = width & 0xff;
857 dtd->part1.h_blank = h_blank_len & 0xff;
858 dtd->part1.h_high = (((width >> 8) & 0xf) << 4) |
859 ((h_blank_len >> 8) & 0xf);
860 dtd->part1.v_active = height & 0xff;
861 dtd->part1.v_blank = v_blank_len & 0xff;
862 dtd->part1.v_high = (((height >> 8) & 0xf) << 4) |
863 ((v_blank_len >> 8) & 0xf);
864
865 dtd->part2.h_sync_off = h_sync_offset & 0xff;
866 dtd->part2.h_sync_width = h_sync_len & 0xff;
867 dtd->part2.v_sync_off_width = (v_sync_offset & 0xf) << 4 |
868 (v_sync_len & 0xf);
869 dtd->part2.sync_off_width_high = ((h_sync_offset & 0x300) >> 2) |
870 ((h_sync_len & 0x300) >> 4) | ((v_sync_offset & 0x30) >> 2) |
871 ((v_sync_len & 0x30) >> 4);
872
873 dtd->part2.dtd_flags = 0x18;
874 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE)
875 dtd->part2.dtd_flags |= DTD_FLAG_INTERLACE;
876 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC)
877 dtd->part2.dtd_flags |= DTD_FLAG_HSYNC_POSITIVE;
878 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC)
879 dtd->part2.dtd_flags |= DTD_FLAG_VSYNC_POSITIVE;
880
881 dtd->part2.v_sync_off_high = v_sync_offset & 0xc0;
882}
883
884static void intel_sdvo_get_mode_from_dtd(struct drm_display_mode *pmode,
885 const struct intel_sdvo_dtd *dtd)
886{
887 static const struct drm_display_mode zero_mode;
888 struct drm_display_mode mode = zero_mode;
889
890 mode.hdisplay = dtd->part1.h_active;
891 mode.hdisplay += ((dtd->part1.h_high >> 4) & 0x0f) << 8;
892 mode.hsync_start = mode.hdisplay + dtd->part2.h_sync_off;
893 mode.hsync_start += (dtd->part2.sync_off_width_high & 0xc0) << 2;
894 mode.hsync_end = mode.hsync_start + dtd->part2.h_sync_width;
895 mode.hsync_end += (dtd->part2.sync_off_width_high & 0x30) << 4;
896 mode.htotal = mode.hdisplay + dtd->part1.h_blank;
897 mode.htotal += (dtd->part1.h_high & 0xf) << 8;
898
899 mode.vdisplay = dtd->part1.v_active;
900 mode.vdisplay += ((dtd->part1.v_high >> 4) & 0x0f) << 8;
901 mode.vsync_start = mode.vdisplay;
902 mode.vsync_start += (dtd->part2.v_sync_off_width >> 4) & 0xf;
903 mode.vsync_start += (dtd->part2.sync_off_width_high & 0x0c) << 2;
904 mode.vsync_start += dtd->part2.v_sync_off_high & 0xc0;
905 mode.vsync_end = mode.vsync_start +
906 (dtd->part2.v_sync_off_width & 0xf);
907 mode.vsync_end += (dtd->part2.sync_off_width_high & 0x3) << 4;
908 mode.vtotal = mode.vdisplay + dtd->part1.v_blank;
909 mode.vtotal += (dtd->part1.v_high & 0xf) << 8;
910
911 mode.clock = dtd->part1.clock * 10;
912
913 if (dtd->part2.dtd_flags & DTD_FLAG_INTERLACE)
914 mode.flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE;
915 if (dtd->part2.dtd_flags & DTD_FLAG_HSYNC_POSITIVE)
916 mode.flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
917 else
918 mode.flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
919 if (dtd->part2.dtd_flags & DTD_FLAG_VSYNC_POSITIVE)
920 mode.flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
921 else
922 mode.flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
923
924 drm_mode_set_crtcinfo(&mode, 0);
925
926 drm_mode_copy(pmode, &mode);
927}

981static bool intel_sdvo_write_infoframe(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo,
982 unsigned if_index, uint8_t tx_rate,
983 const uint8_t *data, unsigned length)
984{
985 uint8_t set_buf_index[2] = { if_index, 0 };
986 uint8_t hbuf_size, tmp[8];
987 int i;
988
989 if (!intel_sdvo_set_value(intel_sdvo,
990 SDVO_CMD_SET_HBUF_INDEX,
991 set_buf_index, 2))
992 return false;
993
994 if (!intel_sdvo_get_value(intel_sdvo, SDVO_CMD_GET_HBUF_INFO,
995 &hbuf_size, 1))
996 return false;
997
998 /* Buffer size is 0 based, hooray! */
999 hbuf_size++;
1000
1001 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("writing sdvo hbuf: %i, hbuf_size %i, hbuf_size: %i\n",
1002 if_index, length, hbuf_size);
1003
1004 for (i = 0; i < hbuf_size; i += 8) {
1005 memset(tmp, 0, 8);
1006 if (i < length)
1007 memcpy(tmp, data + i, min_t(unsigned, 8, length - i));
1008
1009 if (!intel_sdvo_set_value(intel_sdvo,
1010 SDVO_CMD_SET_HBUF_DATA,
1011 tmp, 8))
1012 return false;
1013 }
1014
1015 return intel_sdvo_set_value(intel_sdvo,
1016 SDVO_CMD_SET_HBUF_TXRATE,
1017 &tx_rate, 1);
1018}

1087/* Asks the sdvo controller for the preferred input mode given the output mode.
1088 * Unfortunately we have to set up the full output mode to do that. */
1089static bool
1090intel_sdvo_get_preferred_input_mode(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo,
1091 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
1092 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
1093{
1094 struct intel_sdvo_dtd input_dtd;
1095
1096 /* Reset the input timing to the screen. Assume always input 0. */
1097 if (!intel_sdvo_set_target_input(intel_sdvo))
1098 return false;
1099
1100 if (!intel_sdvo_create_preferred_input_timing(intel_sdvo,
1101 mode->clock / 10,
1102 mode->hdisplay,
1103 mode->vdisplay))
1104 return false;
1105
1106 if (!intel_sdvo_get_preferred_input_timing(intel_sdvo,
1107 &input_dtd))
1108 return false;
1109
1110 intel_sdvo_get_mode_from_dtd(adjusted_mode, &input_dtd);
1111 intel_sdvo->dtd_sdvo_flags = input_dtd.part2.sdvo_flags;
1112
1113 return true;
1114}

1116static void i9xx_adjust_sdvo_tv_clock(struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
1117{
1118 unsigned dotclock = pipe_config->port_clock;
1119 struct dpll *clock = &pipe_config->dpll;
1120
1121 /* SDVO TV has fixed PLL values depend on its clock range,
1122 this mirrors vbios setting. */
1123 if (dotclock >= 100000 && dotclock < 140500) {
1124 clock->p1 = 2;
1125 clock->p2 = 10;
1126 clock->n = 3;
1127 clock->m1 = 16;
1128 clock->m2 = 8;
1129 } else if (dotclock >= 140500 && dotclock <= 200000) {
1130 clock->p1 = 1;
1131 clock->p2 = 10;
1132 clock->n = 6;
1133 clock->m1 = 12;
1134 clock->m2 = 8;
1135 } else {
1136 WARN(1, "SDVO TV clock out of range: %i\n", dotclock);
1137 }
1138
1139 pipe_config->clock_set = true;
1140}

1142static bool intel_sdvo_compute_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
1143 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
1144{
1145 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = to_sdvo(encoder);
1146 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode = &pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode;
1147 struct drm_display_mode *mode = &pipe_config->base.mode;
1148
1149 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("forcing bpc to 8 for SDVO\n");
1150 pipe_config->pipe_bpp = 8*3;
1151
1152 if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(encoder->base.dev))
1153 pipe_config->has_pch_encoder = true;
1154
1155 /* We need to construct preferred input timings based on our
1156 * output timings. To do that, we have to set the output
1157 * timings, even though this isn't really the right place in
1158 * the sequence to do it. Oh well.
1159 */
1160 if (intel_sdvo->is_tv) {
1161 if (!intel_sdvo_set_output_timings_from_mode(intel_sdvo, mode))
1162 return false;
1163
1164 (void) intel_sdvo_get_preferred_input_mode(intel_sdvo,
1165 mode,
1166 adjusted_mode);
1167 pipe_config->sdvo_tv_clock = true;
1168 } else if (intel_sdvo->is_lvds) {
1169 if (!intel_sdvo_set_output_timings_from_mode(intel_sdvo,
1170 intel_sdvo->sdvo_lvds_fixed_mode))
1171 return false;
1172
1173 (void) intel_sdvo_get_preferred_input_mode(intel_sdvo,
1174 mode,
1175 adjusted_mode);
1176 }
1177
1178 /* Make the CRTC code factor in the SDVO pixel multiplier. The
1179 * SDVO device will factor out the multiplier during mode_set.
1180 */
1181 pipe_config->pixel_multiplier =
1182 intel_sdvo_get_pixel_multiplier(adjusted_mode);
1183
1184 pipe_config->has_hdmi_sink = intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_monitor;
1185
1186 if (intel_sdvo->color_range_auto) {
1187 /* See CEA-861-E - 5.1 Default Encoding Parameters */
1188 /* FIXME: This bit is only valid when using TMDS encoding and 8
1189 * bit per color mode. */
1190 if (pipe_config->has_hdmi_sink &&
1191 drm_match_cea_mode(adjusted_mode) > 1)
1192 pipe_config->limited_color_range = true;
1193 } else {
1194 if (pipe_config->has_hdmi_sink &&
1195 intel_sdvo->color_range == HDMI_COLOR_RANGE_16_235)
1196 pipe_config->limited_color_range = true;
1197 }
1198
1199 /* Clock computation needs to happen after pixel multiplier. */
1200 if (intel_sdvo->is_tv)
1201 i9xx_adjust_sdvo_tv_clock(pipe_config);
1202
1203 /* Set user selected PAR to incoming mode's member */
1204 if (intel_sdvo->is_hdmi)
1205 adjusted_mode->picture_aspect_ratio = intel_sdvo->aspect_ratio;
1206
1207 return true;
1208}
1209
1210static void intel_sdvo_pre_enable(struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder)
1211{
1212 struct drm_device *dev = intel_encoder->base.dev;
1213 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1214 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(intel_encoder->base.crtc);
1215 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode = &crtc->config->base.adjusted_mode;
1216 struct drm_display_mode *mode = &crtc->config->base.mode;
1217 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = to_sdvo(intel_encoder);
1218 u32 sdvox;
1219 struct intel_sdvo_in_out_map in_out;
1220 struct intel_sdvo_dtd input_dtd, output_dtd;
1221 int rate;
1222
1223 if (!mode)
1224 return;
1225
1226 /* First, set the input mapping for the first input to our controlled
1227 * output. This is only correct if we're a single-input device, in
1228 * which case the first input is the output from the appropriate SDVO
1229 * channel on the motherboard. In a two-input device, the first input
1230 * will be SDVOB and the second SDVOC.
1231 */
1232 in_out.in0 = intel_sdvo->attached_output;
1233 in_out.in1 = 0;
1234
1235 intel_sdvo_set_value(intel_sdvo,
1236 SDVO_CMD_SET_IN_OUT_MAP,
1237 &in_out, sizeof(in_out));
1238
1239 /* Set the output timings to the screen */
1240 if (!intel_sdvo_set_target_output(intel_sdvo,
1241 intel_sdvo->attached_output))
1242 return;
1243
1244 /* lvds has a special fixed output timing. */
1245 if (intel_sdvo->is_lvds)
1246 intel_sdvo_get_dtd_from_mode(&output_dtd,
1247 intel_sdvo->sdvo_lvds_fixed_mode);
1248 else
1249 intel_sdvo_get_dtd_from_mode(&output_dtd, mode);
1250 if (!intel_sdvo_set_output_timing(intel_sdvo, &output_dtd))
1251 DRM_INFO("Setting output timings on %s failed\n",
1252 SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo));
1253
1254 /* Set the input timing to the screen. Assume always input 0. */
1255 if (!intel_sdvo_set_target_input(intel_sdvo))
1256 return;
1257
1258 if (crtc->config->has_hdmi_sink) {
1259 intel_sdvo_set_encode(intel_sdvo, SDVO_ENCODE_HDMI);
1260 intel_sdvo_set_colorimetry(intel_sdvo,
1261 SDVO_COLORIMETRY_RGB256);
1262 intel_sdvo_set_avi_infoframe(intel_sdvo, adjusted_mode);
1263 } else
1264 intel_sdvo_set_encode(intel_sdvo, SDVO_ENCODE_DVI);
1265
1266 if (intel_sdvo->is_tv &&
1267 !intel_sdvo_set_tv_format(intel_sdvo))
1268 return;
1269
1270 intel_sdvo_get_dtd_from_mode(&input_dtd, adjusted_mode);
1271
1272 if (intel_sdvo->is_tv || intel_sdvo->is_lvds)
1273 input_dtd.part2.sdvo_flags = intel_sdvo->dtd_sdvo_flags;
1274 if (!intel_sdvo_set_input_timing(intel_sdvo, &input_dtd))
1275 DRM_INFO("Setting input timings on %s failed\n",
1276 SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo));
1277
1278 switch (crtc->config->pixel_multiplier) {
1279 default:
1280 WARN(1, "unknown pixel multiplier specified\n");
1281 case 1: rate = SDVO_CLOCK_RATE_MULT_1X; break;
1282 case 2: rate = SDVO_CLOCK_RATE_MULT_2X; break;
1283 case 4: rate = SDVO_CLOCK_RATE_MULT_4X; break;
1284 }
1285 if (!intel_sdvo_set_clock_rate_mult(intel_sdvo, rate))
1286 return;
1287
1288 /* Set the SDVO control regs. */
1289 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 4) {
1290 /* The real mode polarity is set by the SDVO commands, using
1291 * struct intel_sdvo_dtd. */
1292 sdvox = SDVO_VSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH | SDVO_HSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH;
1293 if (!HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev) && crtc->config->limited_color_range)
1294 sdvox |= HDMI_COLOR_RANGE_16_235;
1295 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen < 5)
1296 sdvox |= SDVO_BORDER_ENABLE;
1297 } else {
1298 sdvox = I915_READ(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg);
1299 switch (intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg) {
1300 case GEN3_SDVOB:
1301 sdvox &= SDVOB_PRESERVE_MASK;
1302 break;
1303 case GEN3_SDVOC:
1304 sdvox &= SDVOC_PRESERVE_MASK;
1305 break;
1306 }
1307 sdvox |= (9 << 19) | SDVO_BORDER_ENABLE;
1308 }
1309
1310 if (INTEL_PCH_TYPE(dev) >= PCH_CPT)
1311 sdvox |= SDVO_PIPE_SEL_CPT(crtc->pipe);
1312 else
1313 sdvox |= SDVO_PIPE_SEL(crtc->pipe);
1314
1315 if (intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_audio)
1316 sdvox |= SDVO_AUDIO_ENABLE;
1317
1318 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 4) {
1319 /* done in crtc_mode_set as the dpll_md reg must be written early */
1320 } else if (IS_I945G(dev) || IS_I945GM(dev) || IS_G33(dev)) {
1321 /* done in crtc_mode_set as it lives inside the dpll register */
1322 } else {
1323 sdvox |= (crtc->config->pixel_multiplier - 1)
1324 << SDVO_PORT_MULTIPLY_SHIFT;
1325 }
1326
1327 if (input_dtd.part2.sdvo_flags & SDVO_NEED_TO_STALL &&
1328 INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen < 5)
1329 sdvox |= SDVO_STALL_SELECT;
1330 intel_sdvo_write_sdvox(intel_sdvo, sdvox);
1331}

1348static bool intel_sdvo_get_hw_state(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
1349 enum i915_pipe *pipe)
1350{
1351 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
1352 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1353 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = to_sdvo(encoder);
1354 u16 active_outputs = 0;
1355 u32 tmp;
1356
1357 tmp = I915_READ(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg);
1358 intel_sdvo_get_active_outputs(intel_sdvo, &active_outputs);
1359

1361 return false;
1362

1364 *pipe = PORT_TO_PIPE_CPT(tmp);
1365 else
1366 *pipe = PORT_TO_PIPE(tmp);
1367
1368 return true;

1370
1371static void intel_sdvo_get_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
1372 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
1373{
1374 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
1375 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1376 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = to_sdvo(encoder);
1377 struct intel_sdvo_dtd dtd;
1378 int encoder_pixel_multiplier = 0;
1379 int dotclock;
1380 u32 flags = 0, sdvox;
1381 u8 val;
1382 bool ret;
1383
1384 sdvox = I915_READ(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg);
1385
1386 ret = intel_sdvo_get_input_timing(intel_sdvo, &dtd);
1387 if (!ret) {
1388 /* Some sdvo encoders are not spec compliant and don't
1389 * implement the mandatory get_timings function. */
1390 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("failed to retrieve SDVO DTD\n");
1391 pipe_config->quirks |= PIPE_CONFIG_QUIRK_MODE_SYNC_FLAGS;
1392 } else {
1393 if (dtd.part2.dtd_flags & DTD_FLAG_HSYNC_POSITIVE)
1394 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
1395 else
1396 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
1397
1398 if (dtd.part2.dtd_flags & DTD_FLAG_VSYNC_POSITIVE)
1399 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
1400 else
1401 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
1402 }
1403
1404 pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode.flags |= flags;
1405
1406 /*
1407 * pixel multiplier readout is tricky: Only on i915g/gm it is stored in
1408 * the sdvo port register, on all other platforms it is part of the dpll
1409 * state. Since the general pipe state readout happens before the
1410 * encoder->get_config we so already have a valid pixel multplier on all
1411 * other platfroms.
1412 */
1413 if (IS_I915G(dev) || IS_I915GM(dev)) {
1414 pipe_config->pixel_multiplier =
1415 ((sdvox & SDVO_PORT_MULTIPLY_MASK)
1416 >> SDVO_PORT_MULTIPLY_SHIFT) + 1;
1417 }
1418
1419 dotclock = pipe_config->port_clock;
1420 if (pipe_config->pixel_multiplier)
1421 dotclock /= pipe_config->pixel_multiplier;
1422
1423 if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev))
1424 ironlake_check_encoder_dotclock(pipe_config, dotclock);
1425
1426 pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode.crtc_clock = dotclock;
1427
1428 /* Cross check the port pixel multiplier with the sdvo encoder state. */
1429 if (intel_sdvo_get_value(intel_sdvo, SDVO_CMD_GET_CLOCK_RATE_MULT,
1430 &val, 1)) {
1431 switch (val) {
1432 case SDVO_CLOCK_RATE_MULT_1X:
1433 encoder_pixel_multiplier = 1;
1434 break;
1435 case SDVO_CLOCK_RATE_MULT_2X:
1436 encoder_pixel_multiplier = 2;
1437 break;
1438 case SDVO_CLOCK_RATE_MULT_4X:
1439 encoder_pixel_multiplier = 4;
1440 break;
1441 }
1442 }
1443
1444 if (sdvox & HDMI_COLOR_RANGE_16_235)
1445 pipe_config->limited_color_range = true;
1446
1447 if (intel_sdvo_get_value(intel_sdvo, SDVO_CMD_GET_ENCODE,
1448 &val, 1)) {
1449 if (val == SDVO_ENCODE_HDMI)
1450 pipe_config->has_hdmi_sink = true;
1451 }
1452
1453 WARN(encoder_pixel_multiplier != pipe_config->pixel_multiplier,
1454 "SDVO pixel multiplier mismatch, port: %i, encoder: %i\n",
1455 pipe_config->pixel_multiplier, encoder_pixel_multiplier);
1456}

1458static void intel_disable_sdvo(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
1459{
1460 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = encoder->base.dev->dev_private;
1461 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = to_sdvo(encoder);
1462 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
1463 u32 temp;
1464
1465 intel_sdvo_set_active_outputs(intel_sdvo, 0);
1466 if (0)
1467 intel_sdvo_set_encoder_power_state(intel_sdvo,
1468 DRM_MODE_DPMS_OFF);
1469
1470 temp = I915_READ(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg);
1471
1472 temp &= ~SDVO_ENABLE;
1473 intel_sdvo_write_sdvox(intel_sdvo, temp);
1474
1475 /*
1476 * HW workaround for IBX, we need to move the port
1477 * to transcoder A after disabling it to allow the
1478 * matching DP port to be enabled on transcoder A.
1479 */
1480 if (HAS_PCH_IBX(dev_priv) && crtc->pipe == PIPE_B) {
1481 temp &= ~SDVO_PIPE_B_SELECT;
1482 temp |= SDVO_ENABLE;
1483 intel_sdvo_write_sdvox(intel_sdvo, temp);
1484
1485 temp &= ~SDVO_ENABLE;
1486 intel_sdvo_write_sdvox(intel_sdvo, temp);
1487 }
1488}

1498
1499static void intel_enable_sdvo(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
1500{
1501 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
1502 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1503 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = to_sdvo(encoder);
1504 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
1505 u32 temp;
1506 bool input1, input2;
1507 int i;
1508 bool success;
1509
1510 temp = I915_READ(intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg);
1511 temp |= SDVO_ENABLE;
1512 intel_sdvo_write_sdvox(intel_sdvo, temp);
1513
1514 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
1515 intel_wait_for_vblank(dev, intel_crtc->pipe);
1516
1517 success = intel_sdvo_get_trained_inputs(intel_sdvo, &input1, &input2);
1518 /* Warn if the device reported failure to sync.
1519 * A lot of SDVO devices fail to notify of sync, but it's
1520 * a given it the status is a success, we succeeded.
1521 */
1522 if (success && !input1) {
1523 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("First %s output reported failure to "
1524 "sync\n", SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo));
1525 }
1526
1527 if (0)
1528 intel_sdvo_set_encoder_power_state(intel_sdvo,
1529 DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
1530 intel_sdvo_set_active_outputs(intel_sdvo, intel_sdvo->attached_output);
1531}

1533static enum drm_mode_status
1534intel_sdvo_mode_valid(struct drm_connector *connector,
1535 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
1536{
1537 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = intel_attached_sdvo(connector);
1538
1539 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLSCAN)
1540 return MODE_NO_DBLESCAN;
1541
1542 if (intel_sdvo->pixel_clock_min > mode->clock)
1543 return MODE_CLOCK_LOW;
1544
1545 if (intel_sdvo->pixel_clock_max < mode->clock)
1546 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
1547
1548 if (intel_sdvo->is_lvds) {
1549 if (mode->hdisplay > intel_sdvo->sdvo_lvds_fixed_mode->hdisplay)
1550 return MODE_PANEL;
1551
1552 if (mode->vdisplay > intel_sdvo->sdvo_lvds_fixed_mode->vdisplay)
1553 return MODE_PANEL;
1554 }
1555
1556 return MODE_OK;
1557}

1648
1649static enum drm_connector_status
1650intel_sdvo_tmds_sink_detect(struct drm_connector *connector)
1651{
1652 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = intel_attached_sdvo(connector);
1653 enum drm_connector_status status;
1654 struct edid *edid;
1655
1656 edid = intel_sdvo_get_edid(connector);
1657
1658 if (edid == NULL && intel_sdvo_multifunc_encoder(intel_sdvo)) {
1659 u8 ddc, saved_ddc = intel_sdvo->ddc_bus;
1660
1661 /*
1662 * Don't use the 1 as the argument of DDC bus switch to get
1663 * the EDID. It is used for SDVO SPD ROM.
1664 */
1665 for (ddc = intel_sdvo->ddc_bus >> 1; ddc > 1; ddc >>= 1) {
1666 intel_sdvo->ddc_bus = ddc;
1667 edid = intel_sdvo_get_edid(connector);
1668 if (edid)
1669 break;
1670 }
1671 /*
1672 * If we found the EDID on the other bus,
1673 * assume that is the correct DDC bus.
1674 */
1675 if (edid == NULL)
1676 intel_sdvo->ddc_bus = saved_ddc;
1677 }
1678
1679 /*
1680 * When there is no edid and no monitor is connected with VGA
1681 * port, try to use the CRT ddc to read the EDID for DVI-connector.
1682 */
1683 if (edid == NULL)
1684 edid = intel_sdvo_get_analog_edid(connector);
1685
1686 status = connector_status_unknown;
1687 if (edid != NULL) {
1688 /* DDC bus is shared, match EDID to connector type */
1689 if (edid->input & DRM_EDID_INPUT_DIGITAL) {
1690 status = connector_status_connected;
1691 if (intel_sdvo->is_hdmi) {
1692 intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_monitor = drm_detect_hdmi_monitor(edid);
1693 intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_audio = drm_detect_monitor_audio(edid);
1694 intel_sdvo->rgb_quant_range_selectable =
1695 drm_rgb_quant_range_selectable(edid);
1696 }
1697 } else
1698 status = connector_status_disconnected;
1699 kfree(edid);
1700 }
1701
1702 if (status == connector_status_connected) {
1703 struct intel_sdvo_connector *intel_sdvo_connector = to_intel_sdvo_connector(connector);
1704 if (intel_sdvo_connector->force_audio != HDMI_AUDIO_AUTO)
1705 intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_audio = (intel_sdvo_connector->force_audio == HDMI_AUDIO_ON);
1706 }
1707
1708 return status;
1709}

1711static bool
1712intel_sdvo_connector_matches_edid(struct intel_sdvo_connector *sdvo,
1713 struct edid *edid)
1714{
1715 bool monitor_is_digital = !!(edid->input & DRM_EDID_INPUT_DIGITAL);
1716 bool connector_is_digital = !!IS_DIGITAL(sdvo);
1717
1718 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("connector_is_digital? %d, monitor_is_digital? %d\n",
1719 connector_is_digital, monitor_is_digital);
1720 return connector_is_digital == monitor_is_digital;
1721}
1722
1723static enum drm_connector_status
1724intel_sdvo_detect(struct drm_connector *connector, bool force)
1725{
1726 uint16_t response;
1727 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = intel_attached_sdvo(connector);
1728 struct intel_sdvo_connector *intel_sdvo_connector = to_intel_sdvo_connector(connector);
1729 enum drm_connector_status ret;
1730
1731 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("[CONNECTOR:%d:%s]\n",
1732 connector->base.id, connector->name);
1733
1734 if (!intel_sdvo_get_value(intel_sdvo,
1735 SDVO_CMD_GET_ATTACHED_DISPLAYS,
1736 &response, 2))
1737 return connector_status_unknown;
1738
1739 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SDVO response %d %d [%x]\n",
1740 response & 0xff, response >> 8,
1741 intel_sdvo_connector->output_flag);
1742
1743 if (response == 0)
1744 return connector_status_disconnected;
1745
1746 intel_sdvo->attached_output = response;
1747
1748 intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_monitor = false;
1749 intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_audio = false;
1750 intel_sdvo->rgb_quant_range_selectable = false;
1751
1752 if ((intel_sdvo_connector->output_flag & response) == 0)
1753 ret = connector_status_disconnected;
1754 else if (IS_TMDS(intel_sdvo_connector))
1755 ret = intel_sdvo_tmds_sink_detect(connector);
1756 else {
1757 struct edid *edid;
1758
1759 /* if we have an edid check it matches the connection */
1760 edid = intel_sdvo_get_edid(connector);
1761 if (edid == NULL)
1762 edid = intel_sdvo_get_analog_edid(connector);
1763 if (edid != NULL) {
1764 if (intel_sdvo_connector_matches_edid(intel_sdvo_connector,
1765 edid))
1766 ret = connector_status_connected;
1767 else
1768 ret = connector_status_disconnected;
1769
1770 kfree(edid);
1771 } else
1772 ret = connector_status_connected;
1773 }
1774
1775 /* May update encoder flag for like clock for SDVO TV, etc.*/
1776 if (ret == connector_status_connected) {
1777 intel_sdvo->is_tv = false;
1778 intel_sdvo->is_lvds = false;
1779
1780 if (response & SDVO_TV_MASK)
1781 intel_sdvo->is_tv = true;
1782 if (response & SDVO_LVDS_MASK)
1783 intel_sdvo->is_lvds = intel_sdvo->sdvo_lvds_fixed_mode != NULL;
1784 }
1785
1786 return ret;
1787}

1789static void intel_sdvo_get_ddc_modes(struct drm_connector *connector)

1884static void intel_sdvo_get_tv_modes(struct drm_connector *connector)
1885{
1886 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = intel_attached_sdvo(connector);
1887 struct intel_sdvo_sdtv_resolution_request tv_res;
1888 uint32_t reply = 0, format_map = 0;
1889 int i;
1890
1891 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("[CONNECTOR:%d:%s]\n",
1892 connector->base.id, connector->name);
1893
1894 /* Read the list of supported input resolutions for the selected TV
1895 * format.
1896 */
1897 format_map = 1 << intel_sdvo->tv_format_index;
1898 memcpy(&tv_res, &format_map,
1899 min(sizeof(format_map), sizeof(struct intel_sdvo_sdtv_resolution_request)));
1900
1901 if (!intel_sdvo_set_target_output(intel_sdvo, intel_sdvo->attached_output))
1902 return;
1903
1904 BUILD_BUG_ON(sizeof(tv_res) != 3);
1905 if (!intel_sdvo_write_cmd(intel_sdvo,
1906 SDVO_CMD_GET_SDTV_RESOLUTION_SUPPORT,
1907 &tv_res, sizeof(tv_res)))
1908 return;
1909 if (!intel_sdvo_read_response(intel_sdvo, &reply, 3))
1910 return;
1911
1912 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(sdvo_tv_modes); i++)
1913 if (reply & (1 << i)) {
1914 struct drm_display_mode *nmode;
1915 nmode = drm_mode_duplicate(connector->dev,
1916 &sdvo_tv_modes[i]);
1917 if (nmode)
1918 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, nmode);
1919 }
1920}

1922static void intel_sdvo_get_lvds_modes(struct drm_connector *connector)
1923{
1924 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo = intel_attached_sdvo(connector);
1925 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = connector->dev->dev_private;
1926 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
1927
1928 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("[CONNECTOR:%d:%s]\n",
1929 connector->base.id, connector->name);
1930
1931 /*
1932 * Fetch modes from VBT. For SDVO prefer the VBT mode since some
1933 * SDVO->LVDS transcoders can't cope with the EDID mode.
1934 */
1935 if (dev_priv->vbt.sdvo_lvds_vbt_mode != NULL) {
1936 newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(connector->dev,
1937 dev_priv->vbt.sdvo_lvds_vbt_mode);
1938 if (newmode != NULL) {
1939 /* Guarantee the mode is preferred */
1940 newmode->type = (DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED |
1941 DRM_MODE_TYPE_DRIVER);
1942 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
1943 }
1944 }
1945
1946 /*
1947 * Attempt to get the mode list from DDC.
1948 * Assume that the preferred modes are
1949 * arranged in priority order.
1950 */
1951 intel_ddc_get_modes(connector, &intel_sdvo->ddc);
1952
1953 list_for_each_entry(newmode, &connector->probed_modes, head) {
1954 if (newmode->type & DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED) {
1955 intel_sdvo->sdvo_lvds_fixed_mode =
1956 drm_mode_duplicate(connector->dev, newmode);
1957
1958 intel_sdvo->is_lvds = true;
1959 break;
1960 }
1961 }
1962}

1969 intel_sdvo_get_tv_modes(connector);

2003static int

2007{

2009 struct intel_sdvo_connector *intel_sdvo_connector = to_intel_sdvo_connector(connector);
2010 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = connector->dev->dev_private;
2011 uint16_t temp_value;
2012 uint8_t cmd;
2013 int ret;
2014
2015 ret = drm_object_property_set_value(&connector->base, property, val);
2016 if (ret)
2017 return ret;
2018
2019 if (property == dev_priv->force_audio_property) {
2020 int i = val;
2021 bool has_audio;
2022
2023 if (i == intel_sdvo_connector->force_audio)
2024 return 0;
2025
2026 intel_sdvo_connector->force_audio = i;
2027
2028 if (i == HDMI_AUDIO_AUTO)
2029 has_audio = intel_sdvo_detect_hdmi_audio(connector);
2030 else

2032
2033 if (has_audio == intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_audio)
2034 return 0;
2035
2036 intel_sdvo->has_hdmi_audio = has_audio;
2037 goto done;
2038 }
2039
2040 if (property == dev_priv->broadcast_rgb_property) {
2041 bool old_auto = intel_sdvo->color_range_auto;
2042 uint32_t old_range = intel_sdvo->color_range;
2043
2044 switch (val) {
2045 case INTEL_BROADCAST_RGB_AUTO:
2046 intel_sdvo->color_range_auto = true;
2047 break;
2048 case INTEL_BROADCAST_RGB_FULL:
2049 intel_sdvo->color_range_auto = false;
2050 intel_sdvo->color_range = 0;
2051 break;
2052 case INTEL_BROADCAST_RGB_LIMITED:
2053 intel_sdvo->color_range_auto = false;

2055 * encoding and 8 bit per color mode. */
2056 intel_sdvo->color_range = HDMI_COLOR_RANGE_16_235;
2057 break;
2058 default:
2059 return -EINVAL;
2060 }
2061
2062 if (old_auto == intel_sdvo->color_range_auto &&
2063 old_range == intel_sdvo->color_range)
2064 return 0;
2065
2066 goto done;
2067 }
2068
2069 if (property == connector->dev->mode_config.aspect_ratio_property) {
2070 switch (val) {
2071 case DRM_MODE_PICTURE_ASPECT_NONE:
2072 intel_sdvo->aspect_ratio = HDMI_PICTURE_ASPECT_NONE;
2073 break;
2074 case DRM_MODE_PICTURE_ASPECT_4_3:
2075 intel_sdvo->aspect_ratio = HDMI_PICTURE_ASPECT_4_3;
2076 break;
2077 case DRM_MODE_PICTURE_ASPECT_16_9:
2078 intel_sdvo->aspect_ratio = HDMI_PICTURE_ASPECT_16_9;
2079 break;
2080 default:
2081 return -EINVAL;
2082 }
2083 goto done;
2084 }
2085
2086#define CHECK_PROPERTY(name, NAME) \
2087 if (intel_sdvo_connector->name == property) { \
2088 if (intel_sdvo_connector->cur_##name == temp_value) return 0; \
2089 if (intel_sdvo_connector->max_##name < temp_value) return -EINVAL; \
2090 cmd = SDVO_CMD_SET_##NAME; \
2091 intel_sdvo_connector->cur_##name = temp_value; \
2092 goto set_value; \
2093 }
2094
2095 if (property == intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format) {
2096 if (val >= TV_FORMAT_NUM)
2097 return -EINVAL;
2098
2099 if (intel_sdvo->tv_format_index ==
2100 intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format_supported[val])
2101 return 0;
2102
2103 intel_sdvo->tv_format_index = intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format_supported[val];
2104 goto done;
2105 } else if (IS_TV_OR_LVDS(intel_sdvo_connector)) {
2106 temp_value = val;
2107 if (intel_sdvo_connector->left == property) {
2108 drm_object_property_set_value(&connector->base,
2109 intel_sdvo_connector->right, val);
2110 if (intel_sdvo_connector->left_margin == temp_value)
2111 return 0;
2112
2113 intel_sdvo_connector->left_margin = temp_value;
2114 intel_sdvo_connector->right_margin = temp_value;
2115 temp_value = intel_sdvo_connector->max_hscan -
2116 intel_sdvo_connector->left_margin;
2117 cmd = SDVO_CMD_SET_OVERSCAN_H;
2118 goto set_value;
2119 } else if (intel_sdvo_connector->right == property) {
2120 drm_object_property_set_value(&connector->base,
2121 intel_sdvo_connector->left, val);
2122 if (intel_sdvo_connector->right_margin == temp_value)
2123 return 0;
2124
2125 intel_sdvo_connector->left_margin = temp_value;
2126 intel_sdvo_connector->right_margin = temp_value;
2127 temp_value = intel_sdvo_connector->max_hscan -
2128 intel_sdvo_connector->left_margin;
2129 cmd = SDVO_CMD_SET_OVERSCAN_H;
2130 goto set_value;
2131 } else if (intel_sdvo_connector->top == property) {
2132 drm_object_property_set_value(&connector->base,
2133 intel_sdvo_connector->bottom, val);
2134 if (intel_sdvo_connector->top_margin == temp_value)
2135 return 0;
2136
2137 intel_sdvo_connector->top_margin = temp_value;
2138 intel_sdvo_connector->bottom_margin = temp_value;
2139 temp_value = intel_sdvo_connector->max_vscan -
2140 intel_sdvo_connector->top_margin;
2141 cmd = SDVO_CMD_SET_OVERSCAN_V;
2142 goto set_value;
2143 } else if (intel_sdvo_connector->bottom == property) {
2144 drm_object_property_set_value(&connector->base,
2145 intel_sdvo_connector->top, val);
2146 if (intel_sdvo_connector->bottom_margin == temp_value)
2147 return 0;
2148
2149 intel_sdvo_connector->top_margin = temp_value;
2150 intel_sdvo_connector->bottom_margin = temp_value;
2151 temp_value = intel_sdvo_connector->max_vscan -
2152 intel_sdvo_connector->top_margin;
2153 cmd = SDVO_CMD_SET_OVERSCAN_V;
2154 goto set_value;
2155 }
2156 CHECK_PROPERTY(hpos, HPOS)
2157 CHECK_PROPERTY(vpos, VPOS)
2158 CHECK_PROPERTY(saturation, SATURATION)
2159 CHECK_PROPERTY(contrast, CONTRAST)
2160 CHECK_PROPERTY(hue, HUE)
2161 CHECK_PROPERTY(brightness, BRIGHTNESS)
2162 CHECK_PROPERTY(sharpness, SHARPNESS)
2163 CHECK_PROPERTY(flicker_filter, FLICKER_FILTER)
2164 CHECK_PROPERTY(flicker_filter_2d, FLICKER_FILTER_2D)

2168 CHECK_PROPERTY(dot_crawl, DOT_CRAWL)
2169 }
2170
2171 return -EINVAL; /* unknown property */
2172
2173set_value:

2178done:
2179 if (intel_sdvo->base.base.crtc)

2219static void
2220intel_sdvo_guess_ddc_bus(struct intel_sdvo *sdvo)
2221{
2222 uint16_t mask = 0;
2223 unsigned int num_bits;
2224
2225 /* Make a mask of outputs less than or equal to our own priority in the
2226 * list.
2227 */
2228 switch (sdvo->controlled_output) {
2229 case SDVO_OUTPUT_LVDS1:
2230 mask |= SDVO_OUTPUT_LVDS1;
2231 case SDVO_OUTPUT_LVDS0:
2232 mask |= SDVO_OUTPUT_LVDS0;
2233 case SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS1:
2234 mask |= SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS1;
2235 case SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS0:
2236 mask |= SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS0;
2237 case SDVO_OUTPUT_RGB1:
2238 mask |= SDVO_OUTPUT_RGB1;
2239 case SDVO_OUTPUT_RGB0:
2240 mask |= SDVO_OUTPUT_RGB0;
2241 break;
2242 }
2243
2244 /* Count bits to find what number we are in the priority list. */
2245 mask &= sdvo->caps.output_flags;
2246 num_bits = hweight16(mask);
2247 /* If more than 3 outputs, default to DDC bus 3 for now. */
2248 if (num_bits > 3)
2249 num_bits = 3;
2250
2251 /* Corresponds to SDVO_CONTROL_BUS_DDCx */
2252 sdvo->ddc_bus = 1 << num_bits;
2253}
2254
2255/**
2256 * Choose the appropriate DDC bus for control bus switch command for this
2257 * SDVO output based on the controlled output.
2258 *
2259 * DDC bus number assignment is in a priority order of RGB outputs, then TMDS
2260 * outputs, then LVDS outputs.
2261 */
2262static void
2263intel_sdvo_select_ddc_bus(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
2264 struct intel_sdvo *sdvo)
2265{
2266 struct sdvo_device_mapping *mapping;
2267
2268 if (sdvo->is_sdvob)
2269 mapping = &(dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[0]);
2270 else
2271 mapping = &(dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[1]);
2272
2273 if (mapping->initialized)
2274 sdvo->ddc_bus = 1 << ((mapping->ddc_pin & 0xf0) >> 4);
2275 else
2276 intel_sdvo_guess_ddc_bus(sdvo);
2277}

2279static void
2280intel_sdvo_select_i2c_bus(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
2281 struct intel_sdvo *sdvo)
2282{
2283 struct sdvo_device_mapping *mapping;
2284 u8 pin;
2285
2286 if (sdvo->is_sdvob)
2287 mapping = &dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[0];
2288 else
2289 mapping = &dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[1];
2290
2291 if (mapping->initialized &&
2292 intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(dev_priv, mapping->i2c_pin))
2293 pin = mapping->i2c_pin;
2294 else
2295 pin = GMBUS_PIN_DPB;
2296
2297 sdvo->i2c = intel_gmbus_get_adapter(dev_priv, pin);
2298
2299 /* With gmbus we should be able to drive sdvo i2c at 2MHz, but somehow
2300 * our code totally fails once we start using gmbus. Hence fall back to
2301 * bit banging for now. */
2302 intel_gmbus_force_bit(sdvo->i2c, true);
2303}

2318static u8
2319intel_sdvo_get_slave_addr(struct drm_device *dev, struct intel_sdvo *sdvo)
2320{
2321 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2322 struct sdvo_device_mapping *my_mapping, *other_mapping;
2323
2324 if (sdvo->is_sdvob) {
2325 my_mapping = &dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[0];
2326 other_mapping = &dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[1];
2327 } else {
2328 my_mapping = &dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[1];
2329 other_mapping = &dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[0];
2330 }
2331
2332 /* If the BIOS described our SDVO device, take advantage of it. */
2333 if (my_mapping->slave_addr)
2334 return my_mapping->slave_addr;
2335
2336 /* If the BIOS only described a different SDVO device, use the
2337 * address that it isn't using.
2338 */
2339 if (other_mapping->slave_addr) {
2340 if (other_mapping->slave_addr == 0x70)
2341 return 0x72;
2342 else
2343 return 0x70;
2344 }
2345
2346 /* No SDVO device info is found for another DVO port,
2347 * so use mapping assumption we had before BIOS parsing.
2348 */
2349 if (sdvo->is_sdvob)
2350 return 0x70;
2351 else
2352 return 0x72;
2353}

2452intel_sdvo_dvi_init(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo, int device)
2453{

2457 struct intel_connector *intel_connector;

2459
2460 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("initialising DVI device %d\n", device);
2461
2462 intel_sdvo_connector = intel_sdvo_connector_alloc();
2463 if (!intel_sdvo_connector)
2464 return false;
2465
2466 if (device == 0) {
2467 intel_sdvo->controlled_output |= SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS0;
2468 intel_sdvo_connector->output_flag = SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS0;

2471 intel_sdvo_connector->output_flag = SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS1;

2477 intel_sdvo_connector->output_flag) {
2478 intel_sdvo->hotplug_active |= intel_sdvo_connector->output_flag;
2479 /* Some SDVO devices have one-shot hotplug interrupts.
2480 * Ensure that they get re-enabled when an interrupt happens.
2481 */
2482 intel_encoder->hot_plug = intel_sdvo_enable_hotplug;
2483 intel_sdvo_enable_hotplug(intel_encoder);
2484 } else {
2485 intel_connector->polled = DRM_CONNECTOR_POLL_CONNECT | DRM_CONNECTOR_POLL_DISCONNECT;
2486 }
2487 encoder->encoder_type = DRM_MODE_ENCODER_TMDS;
2488 connector->connector_type = DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_DVID;
2489
2490 if (intel_sdvo_is_hdmi_connector(intel_sdvo, device)) {
2491 connector->connector_type = DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_HDMIA;
2492 intel_sdvo->is_hdmi = true;
2493 }
2494
2495 if (intel_sdvo_connector_init(intel_sdvo_connector, intel_sdvo) < 0) {
2496 kfree(intel_sdvo_connector);
2497 return false;
2498 }
2499
2500 if (intel_sdvo->is_hdmi)
2501 intel_sdvo_add_hdmi_properties(intel_sdvo, intel_sdvo_connector);
2502
2503 return true;
2504}

2628static bool
2629intel_sdvo_output_setup(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo, uint16_t flags)
2630{
2631 intel_sdvo->is_tv = false;
2632 intel_sdvo->is_lvds = false;
2633
2634 /* SDVO requires XXX1 function may not exist unless it has XXX0 function.*/
2635
2636 if (flags & SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS0)
2637 if (!intel_sdvo_dvi_init(intel_sdvo, 0))
2638 return false;
2639
2640 if ((flags & SDVO_TMDS_MASK) == SDVO_TMDS_MASK)
2641 if (!intel_sdvo_dvi_init(intel_sdvo, 1))
2642 return false;
2643
2644 /* TV has no XXX1 function block */
2645 if (flags & SDVO_OUTPUT_SVID0)
2646 if (!intel_sdvo_tv_init(intel_sdvo, SDVO_OUTPUT_SVID0))
2647 return false;
2648
2649 if (flags & SDVO_OUTPUT_CVBS0)
2650 if (!intel_sdvo_tv_init(intel_sdvo, SDVO_OUTPUT_CVBS0))
2651 return false;
2652
2653 if (flags & SDVO_OUTPUT_YPRPB0)
2654 if (!intel_sdvo_tv_init(intel_sdvo, SDVO_OUTPUT_YPRPB0))
2655 return false;
2656
2657 if (flags & SDVO_OUTPUT_RGB0)
2658 if (!intel_sdvo_analog_init(intel_sdvo, 0))
2659 return false;
2660
2661 if ((flags & SDVO_RGB_MASK) == SDVO_RGB_MASK)
2662 if (!intel_sdvo_analog_init(intel_sdvo, 1))
2663 return false;
2664
2665 if (flags & SDVO_OUTPUT_LVDS0)
2666 if (!intel_sdvo_lvds_init(intel_sdvo, 0))
2667 return false;
2668
2669 if ((flags & SDVO_LVDS_MASK) == SDVO_LVDS_MASK)
2670 if (!intel_sdvo_lvds_init(intel_sdvo, 1))
2671 return false;
2672
2673 if ((flags & SDVO_OUTPUT_MASK) == 0) {
2674 unsigned char bytes[2];
2675
2676 intel_sdvo->controlled_output = 0;
2677 memcpy(bytes, &intel_sdvo->caps.output_flags, 2);
2678 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%s: Unknown SDVO output type (0x%02x%02x)\n",
2679 SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo),
2680 bytes[0], bytes[1]);
2681 return false;
2682 }
2683 intel_sdvo->base.crtc_mask = (1 << 0) | (1 << 1) | (1 << 2);
2684
2685 return true;
2686}

2702static bool intel_sdvo_tv_create_property(struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo,
2703 struct intel_sdvo_connector *intel_sdvo_connector,
2704 int type)
2705{
2706 struct drm_device *dev = intel_sdvo->base.base.dev;
2707 struct intel_sdvo_tv_format format;
2708 uint32_t format_map, i;
2709
2710 if (!intel_sdvo_set_target_output(intel_sdvo, type))
2711 return false;
2712
2713 BUILD_BUG_ON(sizeof(format) != 6);
2714 if (!intel_sdvo_get_value(intel_sdvo,
2715 SDVO_CMD_GET_SUPPORTED_TV_FORMATS,
2716 &format, sizeof(format)))
2717 return false;
2718
2719 memcpy(&format_map, &format, min(sizeof(format_map), sizeof(format)));
2720
2721 if (format_map == 0)
2722 return false;
2723
2724 intel_sdvo_connector->format_supported_num = 0;
2725 for (i = 0 ; i < TV_FORMAT_NUM; i++)
2726 if (format_map & (1 << i))
2727 intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format_supported[intel_sdvo_connector->format_supported_num++] = i;
2728
2729
2730 intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format =
2731 drm_property_create(dev, DRM_MODE_PROP_ENUM,
2732 "mode", intel_sdvo_connector->format_supported_num);
2733 if (!intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format)
2734 return false;
2735
2736 for (i = 0; i < intel_sdvo_connector->format_supported_num; i++)
2737 drm_property_add_enum(
2738 intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format, i,
2739 i, tv_format_names[intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format_supported[i]]);
2740
2741 intel_sdvo->tv_format_index = intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format_supported[0];
2742 drm_object_attach_property(&intel_sdvo_connector->base.base.base,
2743 intel_sdvo_connector->tv_format, 0);
2744 return true;
2745
2746}

2952 sdvo->ddc.owner = THIS_MODULE;
2953 sdvo->ddc.class = I2C_CLASS_DDC;
2954 snprintf(sdvo->ddc.name, I2C_NAME_SIZE, "SDVO DDC proxy");
2955 sdvo->ddc.dev.parent = dev->dev;
2956 sdvo->ddc.algo_data = sdvo;
2957 sdvo->ddc.algo = &intel_sdvo_ddc_proxy;
2958
2959 return i2c_add_adapter(&sdvo->ddc) == 0;
2960}

2962bool intel_sdvo_init(struct drm_device *dev, uint32_t sdvo_reg, bool is_sdvob)
2963{
2964 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2965 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder;
2966 struct intel_sdvo *intel_sdvo;
2967 int i;
2968 intel_sdvo = kzalloc(sizeof(*intel_sdvo), GFP_KERNEL);
2969 if (!intel_sdvo)
2970 return false;
2971
2972 intel_sdvo->sdvo_reg = sdvo_reg;
2973 intel_sdvo->is_sdvob = is_sdvob;
2974 intel_sdvo->slave_addr = intel_sdvo_get_slave_addr(dev, intel_sdvo) >> 1;
2975 intel_sdvo_select_i2c_bus(dev_priv, intel_sdvo);
2976 if (!intel_sdvo_init_ddc_proxy(intel_sdvo, dev))
2977 goto err_i2c_bus;
2978
2979 /* encoder type will be decided later */
2980 intel_encoder = &intel_sdvo->base;
2981 intel_encoder->type = INTEL_OUTPUT_SDVO;
2982 drm_encoder_init(dev, &intel_encoder->base, &intel_sdvo_enc_funcs, 0);
2983
2984 /* Read the regs to test if we can talk to the device */
2985 for (i = 0; i < 0x40; i++) {
2986 u8 byte;
2987
2988 if (!intel_sdvo_read_byte(intel_sdvo, i, &byte)) {
2989 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No SDVO device found on %s\n",
2990 SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo));
2991 goto err;
2992 }
2993 }
2994
2995 intel_encoder->compute_config = intel_sdvo_compute_config;
2996 if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev)) {
2997 intel_encoder->disable = pch_disable_sdvo;
2998 intel_encoder->post_disable = pch_post_disable_sdvo;
2999 } else {
3000 intel_encoder->disable = intel_disable_sdvo;
3001 }
3002 intel_encoder->pre_enable = intel_sdvo_pre_enable;
3003 intel_encoder->enable = intel_enable_sdvo;
3004 intel_encoder->get_hw_state = intel_sdvo_get_hw_state;
3005 intel_encoder->get_config = intel_sdvo_get_config;
3006
3007 /* In default case sdvo lvds is false */
3008 if (!intel_sdvo_get_capabilities(intel_sdvo, &intel_sdvo->caps))
3009 goto err;
3010
3011 if (intel_sdvo_output_setup(intel_sdvo,
3012 intel_sdvo->caps.output_flags) != true) {
3013 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SDVO output failed to setup on %s\n",
3014 SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo));
3015 /* Output_setup can leave behind connectors! */
3016 goto err_output;
3017 }
3018
3019 /* Only enable the hotplug irq if we need it, to work around noisy
3020 * hotplug lines.
3021 */
3022 if (intel_sdvo->hotplug_active) {
3023 intel_encoder->hpd_pin =
3024 intel_sdvo->is_sdvob ? HPD_SDVO_B : HPD_SDVO_C;
3025 }
3026
3027 /*
3028 * Cloning SDVO with anything is often impossible, since the SDVO
3029 * encoder can request a special input timing mode. And even if that's
3030 * not the case we have evidence that cloning a plain unscaled mode with
3031 * VGA doesn't really work. Furthermore the cloning flags are way too
3032 * simplistic anyway to express such constraints, so just give up on
3033 * cloning for SDVO encoders.
3034 */
3035 intel_sdvo->base.cloneable = 0;
3036
3037 intel_sdvo_select_ddc_bus(dev_priv, intel_sdvo);
3038
3039 /* Set the input timing to the screen. Assume always input 0. */
3040 if (!intel_sdvo_set_target_input(intel_sdvo))
3041 goto err_output;
3042
3043 if (!intel_sdvo_get_input_pixel_clock_range(intel_sdvo,
3044 &intel_sdvo->pixel_clock_min,
3045 &intel_sdvo->pixel_clock_max))
3046 goto err_output;
3047
3048 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%s device VID/DID: %02X:%02X.%02X, "
3049 "clock range %dMHz - %dMHz, "
3050 "input 1: %c, input 2: %c, "
3051 "output 1: %c, output 2: %c\n",
3052 SDVO_NAME(intel_sdvo),
3053 intel_sdvo->caps.vendor_id, intel_sdvo->caps.device_id,
3054 intel_sdvo->caps.device_rev_id,
3055 intel_sdvo->pixel_clock_min / 1000,
3056 intel_sdvo->pixel_clock_max / 1000,
3057 (intel_sdvo->caps.sdvo_inputs_mask & 0x1) ? 'Y' : 'N',
3058 (intel_sdvo->caps.sdvo_inputs_mask & 0x2) ? 'Y' : 'N',
3059 /* check currently supported outputs */
3060 intel_sdvo->caps.output_flags &
3061 (SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS0 | SDVO_OUTPUT_RGB0) ? 'Y' : 'N',
3062 intel_sdvo->caps.output_flags &
3063 (SDVO_OUTPUT_TMDS1 | SDVO_OUTPUT_RGB1) ? 'Y' : 'N');
3064 return true;
3065
3066err_output:
3067 intel_sdvo_output_cleanup(intel_sdvo);
3068
3069err:
3070 drm_encoder_cleanup(&intel_encoder->base);
3071 i2c_del_adapter(&intel_sdvo->ddc);
3072err_i2c_bus:
3073 intel_sdvo_unselect_i2c_bus(intel_sdvo);
3074 kfree(intel_sdvo);
3075
3076 return false;
3077}
